<p>Buffy flashed another patent smirk. "Sometimes? Yeah, well that ain't winning you any points Ms. Chase."</p>
<p>"I'll sit with you and the rest of the Scooby gang. How about that?"</p>
<p>"You're learning."</p>
<hr/>
<p>"Xander, if you at least opened your Math text every once in a while you might not fail every single test." Willow explained to her friend as they walked into the cafeteria. "Even Buffy has learned the benefits of studying, even if I have to be there to explain it all to her afterwards. You should join us for a session sometime."</p>
<p>Xander didn't reply, he was too busy looking at Buffy and Cordelia sitting at their usual table eating lunch. Willow quickly noticed the same as they approached the table.</p>
<p>"Hey Buff, glad you could make it for class." Xander greeted the Slayer.</p>
<p>"Hey Buffy. Cordelia." Willow said, taking the seat next to Buffy.</p>
<p>"Hey Wil, glad to see you too Xander." Buffy said quietly. Cordelia nodded at Willow.</p>
<p>"Well gee Buff, you ditch class for what reason? I don't imagine vampires were running around town all morning." Xander took his lunch out of his bag but didn't touch it, staring Buffy down instead.</p>
<p>"And you became my mom when?"</p>
<p>"I'm not your mom, Buffy. I'm your friend and I worry about you, especially when you're out all night with her." Xander retorted, glancing at his ex-girlfriend.</p>
<p>Buffy looked at Xander startled. How did he know? He called my house? Damn it, damn it...I don't want to have this conversation. "You called my house?" She asked, ignoring the Cordelia mention for now.</p>
<p>"Yes. Your mom didn't know where you were. Figured you were at Willow's house."</p>
<p>"So what, now she thinks I'm missing?"</p>
<p>"No, I covered for you. Said I had forgotten you were there."</p>
<p>"Where did you go Buffy?" Willow asked carefully. "I was kinda worried too. I thought you might have gotten into trouble with some vampires."</p>
<p>Buffy turned and looked at Cordelia before turning back to face Willow. Oh god, what is she going to say? Cordelia thought waiting for her lover to speak.</p>
<p>"I stayed at Angel's last night." Buffy eventually said. "I ran into trouble going home, he came to my rescue. I didn't feel like going home after that."</p>
<p>Cordelia visibly relaxed. Okay, that works.</p>
<p>"Buffy, Angel came into the Bronze about a half hour after you left looking for you." Willow said slowly.</p>
<p>Damn.</p>
<p>Buffy looked away from the table exasperated. "What do you guys want from me? So I wasn't at home...I wasn't at Angel's either. I went out and for one night I got myself the hell out of Sunnydale." Looking directly as Xander she continued, "And yeah, Cordelia was with me. Is that okay? Is everyone fine now? Buffy had some off time. She decided to forsake the rules for sake of her birthday. Sorry if I lied...sorry that all my friends can't get along...sorry for being all screwed up." Standing up, she grabbed her book bag and stormed off towards the library.</p>
<p>Xander glared at his ex-girlfriend. "This is your influence, it's like you infect people or something."</p>
<p>Cordelia, who was still reeling from Buffy's frustrated outburst, shot Xander the look of death. "Oh yeah Xander, it's all me. Just what's so wrong about her hanging out with me anyway?"</p>
<p>"What's wrong with Buffy hanging out with you? Let's see...."</p>
<p>"Xander..." Willow warned quickly.</p>
<p>"No Willow, I want to say this."</p>
<p>"Xander, if anyone has a problem, it's you. It's none of your business where Buffy chooses to go and who she wants to hang out with."</p>
<p>"And just why does Buffy want to hang out with you anyway Cordelia? Bribing her with money? Need a personal bodyguard? I don't get it."</p>
<p>"You never get anything Xander Harris. Maybe Buffy and I just connect now, okay? It's just a little hard when someone can't seem to accept that."</p>
<p>Xander turned to Willow. "Do you accept it?"</p>
<p>"It was a little hard at first, but yeah, I accept it Xander. I think you should too. They're friends now." Willow said nodding her head once. "It's pretty bad when Buffy has to lie to us in order to hang out with Cordelia. She wouldn't have to do that if she knew you'd be able to handle it."</p>
<p>"I can play nice if you can Xander." Cordelia said seriously.</p>
<p>"The warped kind of nice we used to have? I guess I can try to deal."</p>
<hr/>
<p>Buffy walked into the library and flung her bag onto the nearest table. "Giles? You here?"</p>
<p>Walking out of his office, Giles noticed the anger practically radiating off of the Slayer. "Buffy, I'm glad to see you. Faith should be here right away."</p>
<p>"Yeah. Great. Is there anything going on?" Buffy climbed up onto the table and sat cross-legged waiting for Giles to give her any excuse to think about something, anything else.</p>
<p>"Ah, well you know that it's only been two days since...no, there's nothing new. It's not like you to ask, is everything alright?"</p>
<p>"I'm fine."</p>
<p>Knowing the dangers of pushing Buffy too far, Giles decided to leave it at that. Faith entered the library saving Giles from having to reply.</p>
<p>"Ready to rock, B?" Faith asked, tossing her bag on the counter.</p>
<p>Buffy pushed herself off the table and picked up her book bag. "Give me a minute, I have to change."</p>
<p>"Sure, I'll set up. Giles?" Faith and Giles went into the weapon cage to pull out the floor mats and various weapons. Buffy went into Giles' office to change.</p>
<p>After the mats were set in place, Giles took the much used 'Library Closed' sign and placed it outside the doors to the library. Buffy walked out of Giles' office and immediately started warming up with Faith. They started out slow and easy, using this as an alternative to stretching out. Little by little they upped the tempo, soon becoming full out hand-to-hand combat.</p>
<p>"Wow, B you sure have the fire in ya today. What's up?" Faith asked, her breathing a little ragged.</p>
<p>Blocking Faith's backhand, Buffy moved back a little, "Nothing, just the usual life sucks routine."</p>
<p>Connecting with a shoulder hit, Faith narrowed her eyes. "It's not like you to gripe, something really must be digging at you. You got problems with Deadboy again?"</p>
<p>Buffy connected a solid blow to Faith's stomach, "Don't call him that. And no, it's not Angel."</p>
<p>Faith smirked at Buffy from where she was sprawled on the mat. "Really? Because I could have sworn it was about him...you have that look in your eyes B. The look that tells everyone you're super possessive about something."</p>
<p>"Gee Faith, you read me like a book." Buffy said sarcastically. "Maybe I'm just in a really bad mood."</p>
<p>Faith stood up and took her time getting back into fighting stance. "Nah, it's not your style. The only time you get down and show your anger is when you have demon problems to solve. Even then you're solid. This is something personal."</p>
<p>"And totally none of your business."</p>
<p>"Awww...you're not gonna give? Got some new honey you're stylin'? I heard you didn't go home last night." Faith taunted.</p>
<p>Buffy's face clouded over as she stepped closer to Faith. "I'm glad everyone's on the same page now, I wouldn't want someone to be left out on the details of my life. Now let's fight."</p>
<p>Throwing a punch over Faith's head, Buffy felt the anger burn inside of her. What the hell is wrong with everyone? Am I that predictable? Something new comes along and it's horribly wrong for me to take part? Buffy hit the floor hard as Faith tripped her easily.</p>
<p>"I'm fighting, where are you?" Faith teased. "I really got to you, didn't I?"</p>
<p>Glancing around the room, Buffy noted with relief that Giles had retreated from the library. "Don't flatter yourself, it's not just you." Picking herself up off the floor, Buffy looked at the other slayer thoughtfully. "Can I trust you to keep a secret?"</p>
<p>Faith grinned at Buffy, "Finally gonna spill, eh?"</p>
<p>"Shut up."</p>
